data.name: Current_statment
data.value: Provision for taxation is calculated on the basis of taxable income, using the rates applicable for the current tax year (i.e. 33%). The applicable tax also incorporate the other factors, include available rebates and tax credits, if any. Further, the calculated tax charge for the year is compared with the turnover tax under the section 113 of the Income Tax Ordinance, 2001, and the higher of the two is provided in the financial statements.

data.name: Deferred_Statment
data.value: Deferred tax is calculated using the ‘Balance Sheet Liability’ method through using the rates that are expected to apply for the year which the differences are reversed based on the tax rates that have been enacted (or substantively enacted) by the balance sheet date, which is applied on all the temporary differences. These differences arise between the carrying amount of assets and liabilities in the financial statements and the corresponding tax bases, which are used in the computation of taxable profit. The deferred tax liability is generally recognized (for all taxable temporary differences) by considering deferred tax assets, which are recognized to the extent that it is probable that the taxable profits will be available against which the deductible temporary differences, unused tax losses and tax credits can be utilized. Further, it is charged in the profit and loss account, except in the case of items credited or charged to other comprehensive income or equity, in which case it is included in the other comprehensive income or equity.
